09/08/2006
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The leaders of the four parties in the ruling coalition agreed on Tuesday (8 August) to downsize the number of state secretaries in the ministries by over 36 per cent. Prime Minister Calin Popescu Tariceanu recently proposed the restructuring to boost administrative efficiency. The number of secretaries would be slashed from 82 to 52. Seats would be redistributed among the coalition partners. (Ziua - 09/08/06; Rompres, Mediafax - 08/08/06)
